.TH CALLRX 1 "June 2026" "callrx @@VERSION@@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
callrx \- amateur radio callsign lookup via the FCC ULS database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B callrx
.RI [ CALLSIGN ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B callrx lookup
.I CALLSIGN
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B callrx
.B \-\-help
.br
.B callrx
.B \-\-version
.br
.B callrx history
.I CALLSIGN
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B callrx completions
.I SHELL
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B callrx
is a command-line tool for looking up FCC Universal Licensing System (ULS)
amateur radio licenses by callsign.
Data is retrieved from callook.info, which mirrors the official FCC ULS
database and is updated weekly from FCC bulk data.
.PP
Output is a formatted table showing the licensee name, license class,
address, grid square, trustee (for club licenses), grant and expiry dates,
FCC Registration Number (FRN), and a link to the ULS record.
In terminals that support OSC 8 hyperlinks (iTerm2, WezTerm, Windows Terminal,
and others), the ULS URL and FRN are rendered as clickable links.
.PP
A bare callsign argument with no subcommand is treated as shorthand for
.BR "callrx lookup" .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lookup \fICALLSIGN\fR
Look up the given callsign and display the license record.
The callsign is case-insensitive and is normalized to uppercase before the
request is made.
This is also the default action when a bare callsign is provided.
.TP
.B history \fICALLSIGN\fR
Show every past lookup of the given callsign recorded in the local SQLite
cache database, most recent first.
Each entry shows the date and time (UTC), whether the data was fetched live
from callook.info
.RB ( live )
or served from the local cache
.RB ( cached ),
and how long ago the lookup occurred.
.PP
This command reads from the
.I lookup_history
table, which is populated by every
.BR "callrx lookup"
invocation (including cache hits).
Output is empty if no history exists for the callsign or if the cache
database is unavailable.
.TP
.B completions \fISHELL\fR
Print a shell completion script for the given shell to stdout and exit.
.I SHELL
must be one of:
.BR bash ", " zsh ", " fish ", " elvish ", " powershell .
Source the output to enable tab completion for
.BR callrx .
.SH OPTIONS
The following options apply to both the bare-callsign form and the
.B lookup
subcommand.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print the raw JSON response from callook.info, pretty-printed with
two-space indentation.
Useful for piping to
.BR jq (1)
or for debugging.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-raw .
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Print plain-text output with no ANSI color codes or table formatting.
Each field is printed on its own line as
.IR "Label: Value" .
Suitable for piping to
.BR grep (1),
.BR awk (1),
or other scripts.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-json .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-links
Suppress OSC 8 clickable hyperlinks even in terminals that support them.
By default,
.B callrx
auto-detects link support via
.B $TERM
and related environment variables.
This flag forces plain-text URLs regardless of terminal capabilities.
.TP
.B \-\-raw
.RI ( history
subcommand)
Print plain-text history output with no ANSI color codes.
Each entry is printed on its own line as
.IR "DATE TIME  SOURCE  AGE" .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Bypass the local cache and always fetch fresh data from callook.info.
The fresh result is still written to the cache so subsequent lookups
can be served from it.
See
.B CACHE
below.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Look up a callsign (formatted table):
.B callrx W1AW
.TP
Same lookup using the explicit subcommand:
.B callrx lookup W1AW
.TP
Print the raw JSON API response:
.B callrx W1AW \-\-json
.TP
Print plain text without color (for scripts):
.B callrx W1AW \-\-raw
.TP
Extract the operator class with jq:
.B callrx W1AW \-\-json | jq \-r .current.operClass
.TP
Disable clickable links in the output:
.B callrx W1AW \-\-no\-links
.TP
Show lookup history for a callsign:
.B callrx history W1AW
.TP
Show history as plain text (for scripts):
.B callrx history W1AW \-\-raw
.TP
Install zsh completions:
.B callrx completions zsh > ~/.zsh/completions/_callrx
.TP
Install bash completions (current session):
.B eval "$(callrx completions bash)"
.SH CACHE
.B callrx
caches every successful lookup in a local SQLite database for 7 days,
matching callook.info's weekly FCC bulk-data sync schedule.
Cached lookups are served instantly and display a
.I "Cached X ago"
note in the output.
.PP
The database is stored at:
.IP \(bu 4
.B macOS:
.I ~/Library/Caches/callrx/callrx.db
.IP \(bu 4
.B Linux:
.I ~/.cache/callrx/callrx.db
(or
.IR $XDG_CACHE_HOME /callrx/callrx.db
if set)
.IP \(bu 4
.B Windows:
.I %LOCALAPPDATA%\callrx\callrx.db
.PP
Use
.B \-\-no\-cache
to bypass the read and force a fresh fetch.
The fresh result is still written back so the next lookup benefits from it.
Every lookup (cached or live) is recorded in the
.I lookup_history
table for use by
.BR "callrx history" .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The callsign was found and its license record was printed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred: the callsign was not found in the FCC ULS database,
a network error occurred while contacting callook.info, or the arguments
were invalid.
.SH DATA SOURCE
License data is provided by
.BR callook.info ,
a third-party mirror of the FCC Universal Licensing System database
maintained at \fIhttps://callook.info\fR.
The database is refreshed weekly from FCC bulk data releases.
.B callrx
is not affiliated with callook.info or the FCC.
.PP
FCC license records can also be searched directly at:
.br
\fIhttps://wireless2.fcc.gov/UlsApp/UlsSearch/\fR
.SH OPERATOR CLASS CODES
callook.info reports the operator class as a full word.
The following classes are recognized:
.TP
.B EXTRA
Amateur Extra (highest class)
.TP
.B ADVANCED
Advanced
.TP
.B GENERAL
General
.TP
.B TECHNICIAN
Technician (or Technician Plus)
.TP
.B NOVICE
Novice
.PP
The single-letter FCC codes
.RB ( E ", " A ", " G ", " T ", " N )
are also accepted.
.SH LIMITATIONS
.IP \(bu 4
Only US callsigns in the FCC ULS are supported.
Canadian (Industry Canada), UK (Ofcom), and other DX callsigns are not
available through callook.info.
.IP \(bu 4
License data may be up to one week out of date, as callook.info syncs
from FCC bulk data on a weekly schedule.
.IP \(bu 4
Lookups are cached locally for 7 days.
Use
.B \-\-no\-cache
to force a fresh fetch from callook.info.
.IP \(bu 4
The expired-license indicator uses an approximate date calculation
(leap years are approximated) and is a display hint only.
.SH AUTHORS
Written by John Smith III.
.PP
Source code and issue tracker:
.br
\fIhttps://github.com/binarynoir/callrx\fR
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR jq (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR curl (1)
